PHASE 4 VERIFICATION
====================
  All 8 fixes verified by re-reading modified files:
  - schools.py: asyncio imported, _pss_lock = asyncio.Lock(), async with _pss_lock
  - cms_care_compare.py: asyncio imported, both locks = asyncio.Lock(), async with
  - census.py: B25070_011E absent from all 3 cost-burdened sums; haversine single-call
  - analysis.py: docstring reads "urban -8"
  - main.py: housing weights 0.40/0.30/0.20/0.10; elder_care split by mode with occupancy

  No test suite found in repository to run automated verification.


NOTES:
  - Portfolio workspace endpoints (create, update, compare-snapshot) rely on
    get_session() auto-commit — confirmed correct by reading db/connection.py.
  - delete_history_record (main.py:966) has an explicit commit() inside
    get_session() auto-commit context — redundant but harmless (no-op double
    commit). Not flagged as a bug.
  - The compare endpoint (/api/analyze/compare) does not call
    _enrich_analysis_result, but it only extracts fields that are set by
    _run_analysis, so this is fine for its use case.
  - schools.py lon_buf uses /50.0 (approximate) vs census.py's more accurate
    /69.0*cos(lat). Both are bounding-box pre-filters; the looser approximation
    in schools.py is acceptable since haversine does the precise filtering.
